34#ifndef _VENDORID_H
35#define _VENDORID_H
36
37#ifndef BIT
38#define BIT(x) (1 << (x))
39#endif
40
41/* The unknown vendor ID. */
42#define VENDORID_UNKNOWN -1
43
44/* Our default vendor ID. */
45#define VENDORID_DEFAULT VENDORID_IPSEC_TOOLS
46
47#define VENDORID_IPSEC_TOOLS 0
48
49/* Refer to draft-ietf-ipsec-isakmp-gss-auth-06.txt. */
50#define VENDORID_GSSAPI_LONG 1
51#define VENDORID_GSSAPI 2
52#define VENDORID_MS_NT5 3
53
54#define VENDORID_GSSAPI_MASK (BIT(VENDORID_GSSAPI_LONG) | \
55 BIT(VENDORID_GSSAPI) | \
56 BIT(VENDORID_MS_NT5))
57
58/* NAT-T support */
59#define VENDORID_NATT_00 4
60#define VENDORID_NATT_01 5
61#define VENDORID_NATT_02 6
62#define VENDORID_NATT_02_N 7
63#define VENDORID_NATT_03 8
64#define VENDORID_NATT_04 9
65#define VENDORID_NATT_05 10
66#define VENDORID_NATT_06 11
67#define VENDORID_NATT_07 12
68#define VENDORID_NATT_08 13
69#define VENDORID_NATT_RFC 14
70
71#define VENDORID_NATT_FIRST VENDORID_NATT_00
72#define VENDORID_NATT_LAST VENDORID_NATT_RFC
73
74#define MAX_NATT_VID_COUNT (VENDORID_NATT_LAST - VENDORID_NATT_FIRST + 1)
75
76/* Hybrid auth */
77#define VENDORID_XAUTH 15
78#define VENDORID_UNITY 16
79
80/* IKE fragmentation */
81#define VENDORID_FRAG 17
82
83/* Dead Peer Detection */
84#define VENDORID_DPD 18
85
86
87/* Other Vendors...
88 * XXX: do some cleanup to have separate lists for "real" vendors (to complete)
89 * and "features" VendorIDs
90 */
91#define VENDORID_KAME 19
92
93struct vendor_id {
94 int id;
95 const char *string;
96 vchar_t *hash;
97};
98
99vchar_t *set_vendorid __P((int));
100int handle_vendorid __P((struct ph1handle *, struct isakmp_gen *));
101
102void compute_vendorids __P((void));
103const char *vid_string_by_id __P((int id));
104
105#endif /* _VENDORID_H */
